7. Using the code for GetInteger and the boolalpha stream manipulator, write a function
GetBoolean that waits for the user to enter “true” or “false” and returns the corresponding
boolean value.

Answer:
bool GetBoolean() {
    while(true) {
        stringstream converter;
        bool result;
        
        converter << boolalpha << GetLine();
        if(converter >> result) {
            char remaining;
            if(converter >> remaining)
                cout << "Too many characters: " << remaining << endl;
            else
                return result;
        } else 
            cout << "Retry: ";
    }
}
